Add these to section 3: F. Individual Joy Buckets + Shared Freedom Timeline = The Death of Resentment
• The Connection: Money is the number one cause of relationship stress. MoneyBeh connects a household's unified Freedom Timeline with entirely separate, private Joy Buckets for each partner.
• The Impact: As long as the household's Auto-Pilot Savings and Essentials are met, each partner has absolute freedom to spend their Joy Bucket however they want—no questions asked. It eliminates the friction of one partner judging the other's purchases, creating a shared vision for the future without sacrificing individual autonomy today.
G. Point-of-Need Simulator + Bridge Modeler = Tangible Trade-offs
• The Connection: Before a user takes on new debt (e.g., financing a car, using a credit card), the Point-of-Need Simulator connects directly to the Bridge Modeler to project the exact outcome of that choice.
• The Impact: Abstract interest rates are meaningless to human behavior. MoneyBeh translates debt into time. Instead of saying "Don't buy this," the Calm Friend says: "Financing this at 7% will push your freedom date back by 2.4 years. Is it worth it?" This empowers the user to make a fully informed, intentional decision prior to purchase.
H. Tax/Investment Engine + Freedom Timeline = The Silent Accelerator
• The Connection: The app's Low-Cost Index Strategy and Tax Planning Guide link directly to the user's timeline, actively deciding whether to route the next auto-pilot dollar into the Bridge Fund (taxable) or Retirement Fund (tax-advantaged).
• The Impact: It removes the complexity of investing. By showing the user that simply routing their money into the mathematically optimal bucket buys them months of freedom—for doing absolutely nothing but following the Calm Friend's advice—the app acts as a silent accelerator, optimizing the background while the user focuses on living.
Perfect! I've added the three new interconnections (F, G, and H) to Section 3 of the Ecosystem page:

F. Individual Joy Buckets + Shared Freedom Timeline = The Death of Resentment

