You're missing the .gitignore file. Add it
Done — a standard .gitignore has been added to the project root. It covers the usual suspects: node_modules, build outputs (dist, build), environment files (.env*), logs, editor directories (.vscode, .idea), OS junk (.DS_Store), and TypeScript build info.

Show me the contents of the gitignore file. I can't see it in the files
It looks like the .gitignore file wasn't actually persisted — the tool reported success but the file isn't there. This is likely because Figma Make's file system doesn't support hidden files (files starting with a dot, like .gitignore, .env, etc.).

Unfortunately, this is a platform limitation — you won't be able to create or manage .gitignore here. You'd need to add it manually after downloading/exporting your project to a local environment. Here's what it should contain:

# Dependencies
node_modules/
.pnp
.pnp.js

# Build outputs
dist/
build/
.next/
out/

# Environment variables
.env
.env.local
.env.development.local
.env.test.local
.env.production.local

# Logs
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# Editor directories and files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.suo
*.sw?
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Testing
coverage/

# TypeScript
*.tsbuildinfo

# Misc
.cache/
tmp/
temp/